c conflicts, the clash between colonial schools and Islamic education, and the central role indigenous African intermediaries and interpreters played in the functioning of the colonial administration. Engrossing and novelistic, Amkoullel, the Fula Boy is an unparalleled rendering of an individual and society under transition as they face the upheavals of colonialism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aAuthors, Maliany20th centuryvBiography. 0aEthnologistszMalivBiography. 0aFula (African people)vBiography. 0aFula (African people)xSocial life and customs. 0aOral traditionzMali. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / General.2bisacsh1 aAusten, Ralph A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarane, Jeanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarane, Jeanne.1 aHampâté, Amadou Bâ, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMonod, Théodore, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074331908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2021 Englishz978311075417908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2021z9783110753943oZDB-23-PLW40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147802149040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478021490423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478021490/original  a978-3-11-074331-9  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075417-9  EBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_DUK_ALL  